This file should contain a SOPS-encrypted cryptographic-grade secret
used for encrypting user's PINs. For example, to generate this file
you may use the following commands:

$ echo -n "$(openssl rand -base64 32)" > pin-protection-secret
$ sops encrypt pin-protection-secret > pin-protection-secret.encrypted
$ shred -z pin-protection-secret
$ rm pin-protection-secret
